         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>106</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>236</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Das sittliche Verhalten [hat] das eigene Selbst [= einen] mit Zierden auf jede Weise geziert.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The moral conduct [has?] adorned [one's] own self [= oneself] in every manner.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>311</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>48</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">death [is] well arrived. I am ready [and] do not fear [it].</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">As long as he has not driven off all kleśas, fear for the saṃsāra is still evoked by him.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>710</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Solange er nicht alle Kleśas vertrieben haben sollte, solange wird von ihm noch Furcht vor dem Saṃsāra hervorgerufen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">As long as he should not have expelled all kleśas, just as long fear of the saṃsāra will still be stirred up by him.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>260</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>122, 282</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>30, 96</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>17</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>31, 97</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1995"/><citedRange>60</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>735</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
